{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"For the last 10 years, I've been spending my time trying to figure out"},{"time":3000,"text":"how and why human beings"},{"time":5000,"text":"assemble themselves into social networks."},{"time":8000,"text":"And the kind of social network I'm talking about"},{"time":10000,"text":"is not the recent online variety,"},{"time":12000,"text":"but rather, the kind of social networks"},{"time":14000,"text":"that human beings have been assembling for hundreds of thousands of years,"},{"time":17000,"text":"ever since we emerged from the African savannah."},{"time":20000,"text":"So, I form friendships and co-worker"},{"time":22000,"text":"and sibling and relative relationships with other people"},{"time":25000,"text":"who in turn have similar relationships with other people."},{"time":27000,"text":"And this spreads on out endlessly into a distance."},{"time":30000,"text":"And you get a network that looks like this."},{"time":32000,"text":"Every dot is a person."},{"time":34000,"text":"Every line between them is a relationship between two people --"},{"time":36000,"text":"different kinds of relationships."},{"time":38000,"text":"And you can get this kind of vast fabric of humanity,"},{"time":41000,"text":"in which we're all embedded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"And my colleague, James Fowler and I have been studying for quite sometime"},{"time":46000,"text":"what are the mathematical, social,"},{"time":48000,"text":"biological and psychological rules"},{"time":51000,"text":"that govern how these networks are assembled"},{"time":53000,"text":"and what are the similar rules"},{"time":55000,"text":"that govern how they operate, how they affect our lives."},{"time":58000,"text":"But recently, we've been wondering"},{"time":60000,"text":"whether it might be possible to take advantage of this insight,"},{"time":63000,"text":"to actually find ways to improve the world,"},{"time":65000,"text":"to do something better,"},{"time":67000,"text":"to actually fix things, not just understand things."},{"time":70000,"text":"So one of the first things we thought we would tackle"},{"time":73000,"text":"would be how we go about predicting epidemics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"And the current state of the art in predicting an epidemic --"},{"time":78000,"text":"if you're the CDC or some other national body --"},{"time":81000,"text":"is to sit in the middle where you are"},{"time":83000,"text":"and collect data"},{"time":85000,"text":"from physicians and laboratories in the field"},{"time":87000,"text":"that report the prevalence or the incidence of certain conditions."},{"time":90000,"text":"So, so and so patients have been diagnosed with something,"},{"time":93000,"text":"or other patients have been diagnosed,"},{"time":95000,"text":"and all these data are fed into a central repository, with some delay."},{"time":98000,"text":"And if everything goes smoothly,"},{"time":100000,"text":"one to two weeks from now"},{"time":102000,"text":"you'll know where the epidemic was today."},{"time":105000,"text":"And actually, about a year or so ago,"},{"time":107000,"text":"there was this promulgation"},{"time":109000,"text":"of the idea of Google Flu Trends, with respect to the flu,"},{"time":112000,"text":"where by looking at people's searching behavior today,"},{"time":115000,"text":"we could know where the flu --"},{"time":117000,"text":"what the status of the epidemic was today,"},{"time":119000,"text":"what's the prevalence of the epidemic today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"But what I'd like to show you today"},{"time":124000,"text":"is a means by which we might get"},{"time":126000,"text":"not just rapid warning about an epidemic,"},{"time":129000,"text":"but also actually"},{"time":131000,"text":"early detection of an epidemic."},{"time":133000,"text":"And, in fact, this idea can be used"},{"time":135000,"text":"not just to predict epidemics of germs,"},{"time":138000,"text":"but also to predict epidemics of all sorts of kinds."},{"time":142000,"text":"For example, anything that spreads by a form of social contagion"},{"time":145000,"text":"could be understood in this way,"},{"time":147000,"text":"from abstract ideas on the left"},{"time":149000,"text":"like patriotism, or altruism, or religion"},{"time":152000,"text":"to practices"},{"time":154000,"text":"like dieting behavior, or book purchasing,"},{"time":156000,"text":"or drinking, or bicycle-helmet [and] other safety practices,"},{"time":159000,"text":"or products that people might buy,"},{"time":161000,"text":"purchases of electronic goods,"},{"time":163000,"text":"anything in which there's kind of an interpersonal spread."},{"time":166000,"text":"A kind of a diffusion of innovation"},{"time":168000,"text":"could be understood and predicted"},{"time":170000,"text":"by the mechanism I'm going to show you now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"So, as all of you probably know,"},{"time":175000,"text":"the classic way of thinking about this"},{"time":177000,"text":"is the diffusion-of-innovation,"},{"time":179000,"text":"or the adoption curve."},{"time":181000,"text":"So here on the Y-axis, we have the percent of the people affected,"},{"time":183000,"text":"and on the X-axis, we have time."},{"time":185000,"text":"And at the very beginning, not too many people are affected,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and you get this classic sigmoidal,"},{"time":190000,"text":"or S-shaped, curve."},{"time":192000,"text":"And the reason for this shape is that at the very beginning,"},{"time":194000,"text":"let's say one or two people"},{"time":196000,"text":"are infected, or affected by the thing"},{"time":198000,"text":"and then they affect, or infect, two people,"},{"time":200000,"text":"who in turn affect four, eight, 16 and so forth,"},{"time":203000,"text":"and you get the epidemic growth phase of the curve."},{"time":206000,"text":"And eventually, you saturate the population."},{"time":208000,"text":"There are fewer and fewer people"},{"time":210000,"text":"who are still available that you might infect,"},{"time":212000,"text":"and then you get the plateau of the curve,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and you get this classic sigmoidal curve."},{"time":217000,"text":"And this holds for germs, ideas,"},{"time":219000,"text":"product adoption, behaviors,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and the like."},{"time":223000,"text":"But things don't just diffuse in human populations at random."},{"time":226000,"text":"They actually diffuse through networks."},{"time":228000,"text":"Because, as I said, we live our lives in networks,"},{"time":231000,"text":"and these networks have a particular kind of a structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"Now if you look at a network like this --"},{"time":236000,"text":"this is 105 people."},{"time":238000,"text":"And the lines represent -- the dots are the people,"},{"time":240000,"text":"and the lines represent friendship relationships."},{"time":242000,"text":"You might see that people occupy"},{"time":244000,"text":"different locations within the network."},{"time":246000,"text":"And there are different kinds of relationships between the people."},{"time":248000,"text":"You could have friendship relationships, sibling relationships,"},{"time":251000,"text":"spousal relationships, co-worker relationships,"},{"time":254000,"text":"neighbor relationships and the like."},{"time":257000,"text":"And different sorts of things"},{"time":259000,"text":"spread across different sorts of ties."},{"time":261000,"text":"For instance, sexually transmitted diseases"},{"time":263000,"text":"will spread across sexual ties."},{"time":265000,"text":"Or, for instance, people's smoking behavior"},{"time":267000,"text":"might be influenced by their friends."},{"time":269000,"text":"Or their altruistic or their charitable giving behavior"},{"time":271000,"text":"might be influenced by their coworkers,"},{"time":273000,"text":"or by their neighbors."},{"time":275000,"text":"But not all positions in the network are the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"So if you look at this, you might immediately grasp"},{"time":280000,"text":"that different people have different numbers of connections."},{"time":283000,"text":"Some people have one connection, some have two,"},{"time":285000,"text":"some have six, some have 10 connections."},{"time":288000,"text":"And this is called the \"degree\" of a node,"},{"time":290000,"text":"or the number of connections that a node has."},{"time":292000,"text":"But in addition, there's something else."},{"time":294000,"text":"So, if you look at nodes A and B,"},{"time":296000,"text":"they both have six connections."},{"time":298000,"text":"But if you can see this image [of the network] from a bird's eye view,"},{"time":301000,"text":"you can appreciate that there's something very different"},{"time":303000,"text":"about nodes A and B."},{"time":305000,"text":"So, let me ask you this -- I can cultivate this intuition by asking a question --"},{"time":308000,"text":"who would you rather be"},{"time":310000,"text":"if a deadly germ was spreading through the network, A or B?"},{"time":313000,"text":"(Audience: B.) Nicholas Christakis: B, it's obvious."},{"time":315000,"text":"B is located on the edge of the network."},{"time":317000,"text":"Now, who would you rather be"},{"time":319000,"text":"if a juicy piece of gossip were spreading through the network?"},{"time":322000,"text":"A. And you have an immediate appreciation"},{"time":325000,"text":"that A is going to be more likely"},{"time":327000,"text":"to get the thing that's spreading and to get it sooner"},{"time":330000,"text":"by virtue of their structural location within the network."},{"time":333000,"text":"A, in fact, is more central,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and this can be formalized mathematically."},{"time":338000,"text":"So, if we want to track something"},{"time":340000,"text":"that was spreading through a network,"},{"time":343000,"text":"what we ideally would like to do is to set up sensors"},{"time":345000,"text":"on the central individuals within the network,"},{"time":347000,"text":"including node A,"},{"time":349000,"text":"monitor those people that are right there in the middle of the network,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and somehow get an early detection"},{"time":354000,"text":"of whatever it is that is spreading through the network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357000,"text":"So if you saw them contract a germ or a piece of information,"},{"time":360000,"text":"you would know that, soon enough,"},{"time":362000,"text":"everybody was about to contract this germ"},{"time":364000,"text":"or this piece of information."},{"time":366000,"text":"And this would be much better"},{"time":368000,"text":"than monitoring six randomly chosen people,"},{"time":370000,"text":"without reference to the structure of the population."},{"time":373000,"text":"And in fact, if you could do that,"},{"time":375000,"text":"what you would see is something like this."},{"time":377000,"text":"On the left-hand panel, again, we have the S-shaped curve of adoption."},{"time":380000,"text":"In the dotted red line, we show"},{"time":382000,"text":"what the adoption would be in the random people,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and in the left-hand line, shifted to the left,"},{"time":387000,"text":"we show what the adoption would be"},{"time":389000,"text":"in the central individuals within the network."},{"time":391000,"text":"On the Y-axis is the cumulative instances of contagion,"},{"time":393000,"text":"and on the X-axis is the time."},{"time":395000,"text":"And on the right-hand side, we show the same data,"},{"time":397000,"text":"but here with daily incidence."},{"time":399000,"text":"And what we show here is -- like, here --"},{"time":401000,"text":"very few people are affected, more and more and more and up to here,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and here's the peak of the epidemic."},{"time":405000,"text":"But shifted to the left is what's occurring in the central individuals."},{"time":407000,"text":"And this difference in time between the two"},{"time":410000,"text":"is the early detection, the early warning we can get,"},{"time":413000,"text":"about an impending epidemic"},{"time":415000,"text":"in the human population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"The problem, however,"},{"time":419000,"text":"is that mapping human social networks"},{"time":421000,"text":"is not always possible."},{"time":423000,"text":"It can be expensive, not feasible,"},{"time":425000,"text":"unethical,"},{"time":427000,"text":"or, frankly, just not possible to do such a thing."},{"time":430000,"text":"So, how can we figure out"},{"time":432000,"text":"who the central people are in a network"},{"time":434000,"text":"without actually mapping the network?"},{"time":437000,"text":"What we came up with"},{"time":439000,"text":"was an idea to exploit an old fact,"},{"time":441000,"text":"or a known fact, about social networks,"},{"time":443000,"text":"which goes like this:"},{"time":445000,"text":"Do you know that your friends"},{"time":447000,"text":"have more friends than you do?"},{"time":450000,"text":"Your friends have more friends than you do,"},{"time":453000,"text":"and this is known as the friendship paradox."},{"time":455000,"text":"Imagine a very popular person in the social network --"},{"time":457000,"text":"like a party host who has hundreds of friends --"},{"time":460000,"text":"and a misanthrope who has just one friend,"},{"time":462000,"text":"and you pick someone at random from the population;"},{"time":465000,"text":"they were much more likely to know the party host."},{"time":467000,"text":"And if they nominate the party host as their friend,"},{"time":469000,"text":"that party host has a hundred friends,"},{"time":471000,"text":"therefore, has more friends than they do."},{"time":474000,"text":"And this, in essence, is what's known as the friendship paradox."},{"time":477000,"text":"The friends of randomly chosen people"},{"time":480000,"text":"have higher degree, and are more central"},{"time":482000,"text":"than the random people themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"And you can get an intuitive appreciation for this"},{"time":486000,"text":"if you imagine just the people at the perimeter of the network."},{"time":489000,"text":"If you pick this person,"},{"time":491000,"text":"the only friend they have to nominate is this person,"},{"time":494000,"text":"who, by construction, must have at least two"},{"time":496000,"text":"and typically more friends."},{"time":498000,"text":"And that happens at every peripheral node."},{"time":500000,"text":"And in fact, it happens throughout the network as you move in,"},{"time":503000,"text":"everyone you pick, when they nominate a random --"},{"time":505000,"text":"when a random person nominates a friend of theirs,"},{"time":508000,"text":"you move closer to the center of the network."},{"time":511000,"text":"So, we thought we would exploit this idea"},{"time":514000,"text":"in order to study whether we could predict phenomena within networks."},{"time":517000,"text":"Because now, with this idea"},{"time":519000,"text":"we can take a random sample of people,"},{"time":521000,"text":"have them nominate their friends,"},{"time":523000,"text":"those friends would be more central,"},{"time":525000,"text":"and we could do this without having to map the network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"And we tested this idea with an outbreak of H1N1 flu"},{"time":531000,"text":"at Harvard College"},{"time":533000,"text":"in the fall and winter of 2009, just a few months ago."},{"time":536000,"text":"We took 1,300 randomly selected undergraduates,"},{"time":539000,"text":"we had them nominate their friends,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and we followed both the random students and their friends"},{"time":543000,"text":"daily in time"},{"time":545000,"text":"to see whether or not they had the flu epidemic."},{"time":548000,"text":"And we did this passively by looking at whether or not they'd gone to university health services."},{"time":551000,"text":"And also, we had them [actively] email us a couple of times a week."},{"time":554000,"text":"Exactly what we predicted happened."},{"time":557000,"text":"So the random group is in the red line."},{"time":560000,"text":"The epidemic in the friends group has shifted to the left, over here."},{"time":563000,"text":"And the difference in the two is 16 days."},{"time":566000,"text":"By monitoring the friends group,"},{"time":568000,"text":"we could get 16 days advance warning"},{"time":570000,"text":"of an impending epidemic in this human population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"Now, in addition to that,"},{"time":575000,"text":"if you were an analyst who was trying to study an epidemic"},{"time":578000,"text":"or to predict the adoption of a product, for example,"},{"time":581000,"text":"what you could do is you could pick a random sample of the population,"},{"time":584000,"text":"also have them nominate their friends and follow the friends"},{"time":587000,"text":"and follow both the randoms and the friends."},{"time":590000,"text":"Among the friends, the first evidence you saw of a blip above zero"},{"time":593000,"text":"in adoption of the innovation, for example,"},{"time":596000,"text":"would be evidence of an impending epidemic."},{"time":598000,"text":"Or you could see the first time the two curves diverged,"},{"time":601000,"text":"as shown on the left."},{"time":603000,"text":"When did the randoms -- when did the friends take off"},{"time":606000,"text":"and leave the randoms,"},{"time":608000,"text":"and [when did] their curve start shifting?"},{"time":610000,"text":"And that, as indicated by the white line,"},{"time":612000,"text":"occurred 46 days"},{"time":614000,"text":"before the peak of the epidemic."},{"time":616000,"text":"So this would be a technique"},{"time":618000,"text":"whereby we could get more than a month-and-a-half warning"},{"time":620000,"text":"about a flu epidemic in a particular population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"I should say that"},{"time":625000,"text":"how far advanced a notice one might get about something"},{"time":627000,"text":"depends on a host of factors."},{"time":629000,"text":"It could depend on the nature of the pathogen --"},{"time":631000,"text":"different pathogens,"},{"time":633000,"text":"using this technique, you'd get different warning --"},{"time":635000,"text":"or other phenomena that are spreading,"},{"time":637000,"text":"or frankly, on the structure of the human network."},{"time":640000,"text":"Now in our case, although it wasn't necessary,"},{"time":643000,"text":"we could also actually map the network of the students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"So, this is a map of 714 students"},{"time":647000,"text":"and their friendship ties."},{"time":649000,"text":"And in a minute now, I'm going to put this map into motion."},{"time":651000,"text":"We're going to take daily cuts through the network"},{"time":653000,"text":"for 120 days."},{"time":655000,"text":"The red dots are going to be cases of the flu,"},{"time":658000,"text":"and the yellow dots are going to be friends of the people with the flu."},{"time":661000,"text":"And the size of the dots is going to be proportional"},{"time":663000,"text":"to how many of their friends have the flu."},{"time":665000,"text":"So bigger dots mean more of your friends have the flu."},{"time":668000,"text":"And if you look at this image -- here we are now in September the 13th --"},{"time":671000,"text":"you're going to see a few cases light up."},{"time":673000,"text":"You're going to see kind of blooming of the flu in the middle."},{"time":675000,"text":"Here we are on October the 19th."},{"time":678000,"text":"The slope of the epidemic curve is approaching now, in November."},{"time":680000,"text":"Bang, bang, bang, bang, bang -- you're going to see lots of blooming in the middle,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and then you're going to see a sort of leveling off,"},{"time":685000,"text":"fewer and fewer cases towards the end of December."},{"time":688000,"text":"And this type of a visualization"},{"time":690000,"text":"can show that epidemics like this take root"},{"time":692000,"text":"and affect central individuals first,"},{"time":694000,"text":"before they affect others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696000,"text":"Now, as I've been suggesting,"},{"time":698000,"text":"this method is not restricted to germs,"},{"time":701000,"text":"but actually to anything that spreads in populations."},{"time":703000,"text":"Information spreads in populations,"},{"time":705000,"text":"norms can spread in populations,"},{"time":707000,"text":"behaviors can spread in populations."},{"time":709000,"text":"And by behaviors, I can mean things like criminal behavior,"},{"time":712000,"text":"or voting behavior, or health care behavior,"},{"time":715000,"text":"like smoking, or vaccination,"},{"time":717000,"text":"or product adoption, or other kinds of behaviors"},{"time":719000,"text":"that relate to interpersonal influence."},{"time":721000,"text":"If I'm likely to do something that affects others around me,"},{"time":724000,"text":"this technique can get early warning or early detection"},{"time":727000,"text":"about the adoption within the population."},{"time":730000,"text":"The key thing is that for it to work,"},{"time":732000,"text":"there has to be interpersonal influence."},{"time":734000,"text":"It cannot be because of some broadcast mechanism"},{"time":736000,"text":"affecting everyone uniformly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740000,"text":"Now the same insights"},{"time":742000,"text":"can also be exploited -- with respect to networks --"},{"time":745000,"text":"can also be exploited in other ways,"},{"time":748000,"text":"for example, in the use of targeting"},{"time":750000,"text":"specific people for interventions."},{"time":752000,"text":"So, for example, most of you are probably familiar"},{"time":754000,"text":"with the notion of herd immunity."},{"time":756000,"text":"So, if we have a population of a thousand people,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and we want to make the population immune to a pathogen,"},{"time":762000,"text":"we don't have to immunize every single person."},{"time":764000,"text":"If we immunize 960 of them,"},{"time":766000,"text":"it's as if we had immunized a hundred [percent] of them."},{"time":769000,"text":"Because even if one or two of the non-immune people gets infected,"},{"time":772000,"text":"there's no one for them to infect."},{"time":774000,"text":"They are surrounded by immunized people."},{"time":776000,"text":"So 96 percent is as good as 100 percent."},{"time":779000,"text":"Well, some other scientists have estimated"},{"time":781000,"text":"what would happen if you took a 30 percent random sample"},{"time":783000,"text":"of these 1000 people, 300 people and immunized them."},{"time":786000,"text":"Would you get any population-level immunity?"},{"time":788000,"text":"And the answer is no."},{"time":791000,"text":"But if you took this 30 percent, these 300 people"},{"time":793000,"text":"and had them nominate their friends"},{"time":795000,"text":"and took the same number of vaccine doses"},{"time":798000,"text":"and vaccinated the friends of the 300 --"},{"time":800000,"text":"the 300 friends --"},{"time":802000,"text":"you can get the same level of herd immunity"},{"time":804000,"text":"as if you had vaccinated 96 percent of the population"},{"time":807000,"text":"at a much greater efficiency, with a strict budget constraint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"And similar ideas can be used, for instance,"},{"time":812000,"text":"to target distribution of things like bed nets"},{"time":814000,"text":"in the developing world."},{"time":816000,"text":"If we could understand the structure of networks in villages,"},{"time":819000,"text":"we could target to whom to give the interventions"},{"time":821000,"text":"to foster these kinds of spreads."},{"time":823000,"text":"Or, frankly, for advertising with all kinds of products."},{"time":826000,"text":"If we could understand how to target,"},{"time":828000,"text":"it could affect the efficiency"},{"time":830000,"text":"of what we're trying to achieve."},{"time":832000,"text":"And in fact, we can use data"},{"time":834000,"text":"from all kinds of sources nowadays [to do this]."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836000,"text":"This is a map of eight million phone users"},{"time":838000,"text":"in a European country."},{"time":840000,"text":"Every dot is a person, and every line represents"},{"time":842000,"text":"a volume of calls between the people."},{"time":844000,"text":"And we can use such data, that's being passively obtained,"},{"time":847000,"text":"to map these whole countries"},{"time":849000,"text":"and understand who is located where within the network."},{"time":852000,"text":"Without actually having to query them at all,"},{"time":854000,"text":"we can get this kind of a structural insight."},{"time":856000,"text":"And other sources of information, as you're no doubt aware"},{"time":859000,"text":"are available about such features, from email interactions,"},{"time":862000,"text":"online interactions,"},{"time":864000,"text":"online social networks and so forth."},{"time":867000,"text":"And in fact, we are in the era of what I would call"},{"time":869000,"text":"\"massive-passive\" data collection efforts."},{"time":872000,"text":"They're all kinds of ways we can use massively collected data"},{"time":875000,"text":"to create sensor networks"},{"time":878000,"text":"to follow the population,"},{"time":880000,"text":"understand what's happening in the population,"},{"time":882000,"text":"and intervene in the population for the better."},{"time":885000,"text":"Because these new technologies tell us"},{"time":887000,"text":"not just who is talking to whom,"},{"time":889000,"text":"but where everyone is,"},{"time":891000,"text":"and what they're thinking based on what they're uploading on the Internet,"},{"time":894000,"text":"and what they're buying based on their purchases."},{"time":896000,"text":"And all this administrative data can be pulled together"},{"time":899000,"text":"and processed to understand human behavior"},{"time":901000,"text":"in a way we never could before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"So, for example, we could use truckers' purchases of fuel."},{"time":907000,"text":"So the truckers are just going about their business,"},{"time":909000,"text":"and they're buying fuel."},{"time":911000,"text":"And we see a blip up in the truckers' purchases of fuel,"},{"time":914000,"text":"and we know that a recession is about to end."},{"time":916000,"text":"Or we can monitor the velocity"},{"time":918000,"text":"with which people are moving with their phones on a highway,"},{"time":921000,"text":"and the phone company can see,"},{"time":923000,"text":"as the velocity is slowing down,"},{"time":925000,"text":"that there's a traffic jam."},{"time":927000,"text":"And they can feed that information back to their subscribers,"},{"time":930000,"text":"but only to their subscribers on the same highway"},{"time":932000,"text":"located behind the traffic jam!"},{"time":934000,"text":"Or we can monitor doctors prescribing behaviors, passively,"},{"time":937000,"text":"and see how the diffusion of innovation with pharmaceuticals"},{"time":940000,"text":"occurs within [networks of] doctors."},{"time":942000,"text":"Or again, we can monitor purchasing behavior in people"},{"time":944000,"text":"and watch how these types of phenomena"},{"time":946000,"text":"can diffuse within human populations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"And there are three ways, I think,"},{"time":951000,"text":"that these massive-passive data can be used."},{"time":953000,"text":"One is fully passive,"},{"time":955000,"text":"like I just described --"},{"time":957000,"text":"as in, for instance, the trucker example,"},{"time":959000,"text":"where we don't actually intervene in the population in any way."},{"time":961000,"text":"One is quasi-active,"},{"time":963000,"text":"like the flu example I gave,"},{"time":965000,"text":"where we get some people to nominate their friends"},{"time":968000,"text":"and then passively monitor their friends --"},{"time":970000,"text":"do they have the flu, or not? -- and then get warning."},{"time":972000,"text":"Or another example would be,"},{"time":974000,"text":"if you're a phone company, you figure out who's central in the network"},{"time":977000,"text":"and you ask those people, \"Look, will you just text us your fever every day?"},{"time":980000,"text":"Just text us your temperature.\""},{"time":982000,"text":"And collect vast amounts of information about people's temperature,"},{"time":985000,"text":"but from centrally located individuals."},{"time":987000,"text":"And be able, on a large scale,"},{"time":989000,"text":"to monitor an impending epidemic"},{"time":991000,"text":"with very minimal input from people."},{"time":993000,"text":"Or, finally, it can be more fully active --"},{"time":995000,"text":"as I know subsequent speakers will also talk about today --"},{"time":997000,"text":"where people might globally participate in wikis,"},{"time":999000,"text":"or photographing, or monitoring elections,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and upload information in a way that allows us to pool"},{"time":1004000,"text":"information in order to understand social processes"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and social phenomena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008000,"text":"In fact, the availability of these data, I think,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"heralds a kind of new era"},{"time":1012000,"text":"of what I and others would like to call"},{"time":1014000,"text":"\"computational social science.\""},{"time":1016000,"text":"It's sort of like when Galileo invented -- or, didn't invent --"},{"time":1019000,"text":"came to use a telescope"},{"time":1021000,"text":"and could see the heavens in a new way,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"or Leeuwenhoek became aware of the microscope --"},{"time":1025000,"text":"or actually invented --"},{"time":1027000,"text":"and could see biology in a new way."},{"time":1029000,"text":"But now we have access to these kinds of data"},{"time":1031000,"text":"that allow us to understand social processes"},{"time":1033000,"text":"and social phenomena"},{"time":1035000,"text":"in an entirely new way that was never before possible."},{"time":1038000,"text":"And with this science, we can"},{"time":1040000,"text":"understand how exactly"},{"time":1042000,"text":"the whole comes to be greater"},{"time":1044000,"text":"than the sum of its parts."},{"time":1046000,"text":"And actually, we can use these insights"},{"time":1048000,"text":"to improve society and improve human well-being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}